steps.description:
For caliper brakes, unscrew the small bolt on each side of the caliper brake that is attached to the brake pad itself. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7f/Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/7/7f/Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet1.jpg/aid462976-v4-728px-Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Once the brake pads are removed, unscrew the (smaller) screw on the pad/metal assembly itself, and slide the pad out of the metal piece it is attached to. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/f/f9/Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet2.jpg/aid462976-v4-728px-Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Replace the pad by sliding a fresh one in. This is a worthwhile and inexpensive repair for your bike, since brake pads are cheap and are your best friend on the road. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/05/Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/0/05/Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet3.jpg/aid462976-v4-728px-Take-Apart-a-Track-Bicycle-Step-15Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
